<br>
I've looked for the 'soulbinders' in FP and Felwithe, and they're not in the best spots, if you ask me. Sure, the one in Felwithe is just inside the gate, but the whole zone of G Fay is bind wherever, so bindng in Felwithe is a waste of zoning time.<br>
<br>
As for Freeport, Ailu hit the nail on the head. Most evil races can't get that far into the city, making a bind at the zone edge much more to their liking.<br>
<br>
And, as far as the money issue goes, its all a matter of worth. An item or service is only worth what it's worth to you. For example, if I'm in a hurry to get to somewhere, then 10pp may be a reasonable fee for the TL or TP. Same with a bind. If I can't go into a city to get the free bind at the soulbinders, then anyone willing to come to me deserves some gratuity, because of the convenience for me.<br>
<br>
Sure, mana is free, but time has value.<br>
<br>
