<br>
 Personally , I agree and disagree with many of<br>
these opnions. I thought the druids days as<br>
paid porters would soon be ending too until I<br>
started raking in 100-300 pp every time I logged<br>
my druid on after Luclin. Ports to NK and back <br>
from the moon are in high demand and I was recently<br>
paid 100pp for a port to Iceclad. I think it's too early<br>
to tell how paid binds will be affected till we see where<br>
the Soulbinders are and what the charges are etc. On<br>
the flip side , I welcome the fact that we now have <br>
the possibility of binds closer to camps for our me-<br>
leers and can hopefully avoid some of the extended<br>
downtime form long corpse runs in groups that do<br>
not have a rezzing cleric. This makes for more play<br>
time, more xp,more loot and more fun , IMHO. <br>
<br>
 As a mage, I never made much pp by binding. I <br>
made most of mine shopping and reselling, looting,<br>
and getting the gear I needed from groups with <br>
need before greed philosophy. I found that camp-<br>
ing certain mobs early on ( like the bandits in Lfay<br>
or wisps , hill giants etc) would bring in enough<br>
cash for spells . Donations from friends helped as <br>
well and ,as much as I could ,I shared the wealth <br>
by giving away what I no longer needed or spreading<br>
out the extra pp.<br>
<br>
 There are a myriad of opportunities for making pp<br>
in this game if you are resourceful enough. The shaman<br>
one of my alts groups with makes pp selling stacks<br>
of silks and bone chips, buys molds for banded and <br>
then sells the armor she makes. She is lvl 21 now ,<br>
a master smith, has more than 250 pp in the bank<br>
and has earned every copper of it. <br>
<br>
 I know it's disappointing to see changes in the <br>
game shut down a potential source of revenue<br>
but you create your own opportunities and I see<br>
this as a challenge to finding another and per-<br>
haps even more lucrative way to make $$.<br>
<br>
--Leldara/Alti <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.showMessage?topicID=1531.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.showMessage?topicID=1530.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.emailToFriend?topicID=1528.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.threadControl?topicID=1528.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/sunset/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1528.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub76.ezboard.com/frandomactsgeneraldiscussion.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1528.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub76.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="randomactsfrm6">Fledgling and Prospective Members<option value="randomactsgeneraldiscussion">Guild Roundtable<option value="randomactsmemberinformation">Getting to Know RA<option value="randomactsfrm8">Hurray for . . .<option value="randomactsfrm21">Prize Patrol<option value="randomactsfrm23">Members Only<option value="randomactsfrm7">Council and Officer Discussions <option value="randomactsfrm11">Volunteers o